Floriography: broad, inclusive, handsome

Crassula capitella 'Campfire'
Floriography: passion, vitality, and beauty 
Campfire is a succulent plant, growing in bushes easily to produce collateral branches. The leaves are flat, with short teeth at the edge. The leaf color is yellow green. In cool season and when sunlight is sufficient, leaves turn red, making one feel passionate. 
Campfire like plenty of sunshine, semi shadow resistance. In hot summer, it enters a short dormancy, so place in the shade. It is blossoming from June to July with yellow-white flowers.

Crassula conjuncta
Floriography: stylish, lucky, self-reliant.

Leaves of the C. conjuncta are larger than those of the necklace vine (C. perforata), dark green and thick. Leaf edges are reddish brown or brown if well sunbathed. Leaves stack and offset freely to form large clusters. It is a well-recognized indoor potted foliage plant.

The plant requires sunny habitat. Partial shade tolerant. Summer dormant, protect from direct sunlight. Cream colored flowers bloom in spring.

Crassula fusca
Floriography: enthusiastic, vigorous, vigorous

Crassula lycopodioides
Floriography: vigorous, positive, tenacious

Crassula lycopodioides loves abundant sunlight, tolerates half sunlight, dormant in summer and avoid direct sunlight exposure for better care.

Crassula marnieriana
Floriography: wealthy, lucky, warm.

Crassula marnieriana is a full sun plant and partial shade tolerant. It will go through dormancy in summer and should be remove from direct sunlight to a place with scattered light. It blooms with inconspicuous pale yellow flowers in spring.

Crinum asiaticum
Floriography: generous, classical, loyal

Crocus spp.

Cryptanthus bivittatus 'Red Star'
Floriography: auspicious, passionate, lucky.

Cryptanthus bivittatus 'Red Star' is a genus of flowering plants in the family Bromeliaceae, subfamily Bromelioideae. The genus, named for the Swedish botanist, zoologist, and anatomist Gustaf Johan Billberg. Leaves of Cryptanthus bivittatus 'Red Star' smooth and orderly arranged as a loose lotus flower. Cyclamen coum
Floriography: hospitable, passionate and beautiful. 
Flowers of the cyclamen are unique and bright colored with intensive scent. Dark green heart-shaped possess strips. Though the name of the flower in many languages associated with pig because it was considered as food of pigs, the transliteral Chinese name represents itself as a guest from fairy land. The flower has been adopted in Chinese culture to express hospitality to guests by placing it in hallway, in front of doors of house, living room or bedroom.
Cyclamen prefers places with plenty of sunlight. Move it out of direct sunlight during its dormancy in hot summer. Bloom time goes from November to next May, lasting for two to three weeks. Flowers could bloom again if cutting wilted flowers after bloom.

Hedera canariensis is a genus of 12â15 species of evergreen climbing or ground-creeping woody plants in the family Araliaceae, have aerial roots to absorb moisture and nutrition from the air. Beautiful symmetric leaves. Can be placed in the living room, on desks, or for hanging in pots. 
Hedera canariensis tolerates shade, suitable under scattered light in summer and 3-4 hours sunlight in winter. Blooms sometimes in September to November with pale yellow or green flowers.

Helianthus annuus
Floriogrphy: sunny, warm, and optimistic.

The name sunflower may derive from the fact that shape of the flower's head resembles the sun, or from the false impression that the blooming plant appears to slowly turn its flower towards the sun as the latter moves across the sky on a daily basis. Generally, there is only a single large golden inflorescence atop an unbranched stem like a small sun. The outer flowers, ray flowers, attract pollinators. The tubiform florets in the center of the flower head, disk flowers, mature into edible fruits (sunflower seeds).

Sunflower prefers sunny areas. The flower can grow in any season, however, summer and winter are better. Blooming period is short, lasting for two through three weeks.

The photinia is an evergreen shrub or small tree. Leaves are long round oval, edge slightly toothed, red then turning green after mature. Small delicate flowers bloom clustery with great vitality. It has been widely cultivated for garden uses.

Hibiscus mutabilis
Floriography: noble, delicate, beautiful.
Confederate rose is the official flower of Chengdu city. Leaves crack at tips like a palm. Flowers are single petal or polyphyll, color changing by time from white or light red to dark red.
The plant grows best with plenty of light, slightly shade tolerant. It blooms in August to November for two to three weeks. New branches sprout in spring after dormancy in winter.

Hibiscus rosa-sinensis 
It is the official flower of Nanning. Leaves are emerald green to dark green, elliptic, edges tooth waved. Flowers are mostly red, single petal or polyphyll.
The plant grows best with plenty of sunlight. Shaded accordingly during summer. Flowering all year.

Hibiscus syriacus
Floriography: gentle, pure, beautiful 
Hibiscus syriacus is a hardy deciduous shrub. Leaf shape is nearly the diamond, and with wavy sawtooth on leaf edges. Flower is bell shape, with single or double petal. Color is pure and fresh quietly elegant. Color includes white, pink, lavender, etc. Hibiscus syriacus is used as a hedge, hedge or garden ornament and indoor plants. 
Hibiscus syriacus like plenty of sunshine, a little resistance to shade. Flowering from July to October, with ornamental period, for 2-3 weeks at a time.

Hippeastrum hybridum
Floriography: hot, passionate, loyal
Has beautiful green leaves, scape sprouted from the middle of the leaf blades, one or several huge flowers on the top of scape, exotic and like lilies with beautiful red, orange, pink, or complex color. Commonly used in interior decoration or flower beds.
Hippeastrum hybridum likes the sun with tolerance to half shade, blooms in spring or winter, available for viewing in 2-3 weeks. After flowering, cut the scape and leave the bulbs for sprouting in the next year, normally may bloom for years.

Hosta clausa 
Floriography: tranquil, temperate, pure.
The plant grows delicately upright. Leaves are round heart shaped with gloss. Flowers are produced on erect scapes. The individual flowers are usually pendulous with six petals, white, lavender, or violet in color and strongly fragrant. Garden uses are for pots, flower beds, borders and around ponds.
Grows best in shade with good ventilation under scatter light. Blooms in July to September for one to two weeks.

Hyacinth orientalis 'Blue Jacket ' 
Floriography: vitality, fraternity, self-confidence
Hyacinth orientalis is known as "western narcissus", was cultivated from the flower kingdom of the Netherlands. 
Hyacinth plant state low, inflorescence is plumy, flowers open from bottom to top, appearance beautiful, of quietly elegant fragrance can stabilize mood, eliminate fatigue. It is often put on the head of a bed, to create a warm and comfortable rest environment. 
Hyacinth likes sunshine, full bloom in spring, flowering 3-4 weeks. Keep the bulbs for germination in the coming year in cold, and under normal circumstances it can bloom every year

Hydrangea anomala
Floriography: loyalty, perfect, beautiful 
Hydrangea leaves are green and wide oval. It is rich in color varies from pure color to the gradients of color. Flower pattern is plump, nearly spherical, luxuriant appearance like the bride bouquet. Because of its perfect pattern and implied good meaning, Hydrangea is commonly used in festival decoration or landscape display of parks. 
Hydrangea likes half overcast environment, place under appropriate scattered light. Flowering from June to August and ornamental period up to a month at a time.

Lobelia cardinalis 
Floriography: rationality, freedom, delicate
Lobelia cardinalis is a herb with beautiful lanceolate leaves and flowers of slender petals with elegant colors. Flowers half open, hence named "lobelia". Suitable for flower beds or home landscaping, known for medicinal value of detoxification as well.

Lobelia erinus
Floriography: unique, compact, loyalty

Narcissus bulbocodium is extremely graceful, like a river fairy. Two types: China Narcissus and Daffodils. China Narcissus is the official flower of Zhangzhou City in China.
Chinese narcissus has white flowers, yellow bowl-shaped paracorolla (inner corolla), rich scent. Flowers in winter. Daffodils have many varieties, with varied inner corolla shapes, lighter and elegant scent, bloom normally in April-May.
Narcissus likes sunshine, also resistant to half shade, period of flower viewing 2-3 weeks. After flowering, leave the bulbs for sprouting in the coming year, may normally blossom for years.

Protea 
Floriography: tenacious, wealthy, gorgeous
Protea also known as "Bodhi flower", revered as South Africa's national flower.
Protea has a peculiar shape with oval leaves and huge exotic flowers of a rarely seen form, mimic a rosette, has white to red color. Suitable for potted ornamental planting, can be an ideal material for cut flowers and dried flowers.
Protea likes sunny places, but shade properly under strong summer sunlight. Flowering time from May to December for viewing in 5-7 months.

Rosa chinensis 
Floriography: glamorous, blessed, enthusiastic
Chinese Rose is the official flower of Tianjing City, blooming year around, also called Yue Yue Hong in Chinese, meaning blossoming every month.
Chinese Roses are shrub plants with many varieties. Leaves have 3-5 leaflets, oval, egg-shaped with smooth coating. Flowers are big, with single flowers born in the top of branches, displaying gorgeous color. For this reason, Chinese Rose is regarded as the Queen of Flowers. 
Chinese Rose likes the sun. Flowers last for 2-3 weeks normally. New sprouts emerge soon after pruning.

Rosa foetida

Generally, rose grows in the roadsides, or along with the field, it is also used in decoration of flower beds, flower shelf and tracery wall, etc. 
Rosa foetida maintenance is simple, and it like the sunshine. Flowering from May to September, is available for viewing for 2-3 weeks each period.

Zephyranthes candida 
Floriography: pure, soft, graceful
Zephyranthes candida is an herb, looks like orchids, very graceful, has slender line-like leaves, 6-petal flowers raised above the foliage on top of scape, white as snow. Suitable for flower beds or potted plants for indoor environments.
Zephyranthes candida likes sunny environments, also resistant to half shade. Flowers from June to August with a period of flower viewing 2-3 weeks.

Zinnia angustifolia 
Floriography: warm-hearted, sunny, positive
Zinnia angustifolia will complete its life cycle in one year. Beautiful color. Flower shape is like a small sun, under sunlight, clustered lovely flowers especially dazzling and beautiful. In 2016, a Zinnia angustifolia at the International Space Station was the first flower that bloomed in the outer space.
Zinnia angustifolia likes sunny days, but avoid direct strong sunlight. Flowering from June to October for 3-4 weeks.
